article.description: Utah Valley St pulls away from S. Utah, 85-75
article.headline: Utah Valley St pulls away from S. Utah, 85-75
article.linkText: Utah Valley St pulls away from S. Utah, 85-75
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Mitch Bruneel and Zach Nelson combined to score 51 points as Utah Valley State posted an 85-75 win over Southern Utah Saturday night. Southern Utah (0-3) held a one-point lead at intermission and led by one, 61-60 with under eight minutes to play, but the Wolverines had the stronger finish. Bruneel was 11 of 15 from the field, 2 of 3 from three-point range, and a perfect 3 for 3 from the line to lead Wolverines (2-1). Nelson was 8 of 12 from the field while the team shot a brisk 31 of 55 (56 percent) and 7 of 13 from long range (53.8 percent). A.J. Hess scored 12 points and Cal Hanks added another 11 to lead Southern Utah (0-3). Utah Valley State and Southern Utah now have played five games, with the Wolverines holding a 4-1 advantage in the series.
